There are a few key things you need to do to survive and thrive in the business world of digital.
1) Make sure you have a strong online presence. This means having a well-designed website, being active on social media, and publishing great content that will attract attention.
2) Stay up to date with the latest marketing trends. Keep track of what's working and what's not, and make changes accordingly. Try different tactics and see which ones work best for your business.

Please Provide A Few Paragraphs About Yourself Or Your Business
My name is Stephenie Tornberg. I am a family medicine physician and founder of The ROW Health Co, a wellness clinic for exceptional Health + Care here to provide a better approach to primary health care needs.
The ROW Health Co. understands that to achieve wellness, we need to get to the root of the problem, hence The ROW (Root Of Wellness).
To be able to accomplish this, we have established our clinic to be a part of an innovative movement in health care called Direct Primary Care (DPC). DPC focuses on the highest quality and unprecedented access to care, which directly and positively impacts health outcomes, all while lowering costs to patients. In other words, The ROW Health Co. is going back to the roots of “old time medicine” with a modern twist to provide HEALTH + CARE, uncompromised.
It is a membership-model in which we are bringing health care back to its roots - Patients + Physicians. It eliminates the “middle men,” phone trees, insurance, and other barriers that lie between the patient and physician.
At The ROW Health Co, we provide concierge-style, holistic, integrative and comprehensive direct medical care focused on wellness so our Members can optimize their health and wellbeing with intention! We offer full primary care services, in addition to weight management and breastfeeding medicine (lactation) as our special interest.

accessible and hassle free, extended visits, personalized and comprehensive care, exceptional experience, transparency always
Welcome to The ROW Health Collective. I am ecstatic to begin this journey providing medical care the way it should be. Beginning at the young age of 4, I dreamt of becoming a physician. I do not come from a family of medical professionals or had any traumatic experience that drew me to medicine. It was always a career that drew my attention, from making my mother chase ambulances, to caring for any injured human or animal around me. I volunteered in the Emergency Department, then Certified Nursing Assistant at Overlake Medical Center in Bellevue, WA in high school, then Bozeman Deaconess Hospital in Bozeman, MT as a college student. I was accepted to multiple medical schools, choosing Pacific Northwest University of Health Sciences - College of Osteopathic Medicine in Yakima, WA, a school in its infancy at the time that was just my style – a small and intimate program in which everyone not only knew your name, but knew my family and who I am as a person. I chose MultiCare East Pierce Family Medicine (a dual accredited residency) in Puyallup, WA for residency. I had the privilege to work with MultiCare Health System and Swedish Medical Group after residency, however I was not feeling fulfilled. There is an inherent problem with our structure of medicine. I told her we were having a picnic but it was technically an illegal picnic because we had, ahem, a couple additional people than we were meant to. The idea of an illegal picnic sounded so absurd, that she asked "what the hell do you mean an illegal picnic? Sounds like a skate brand or something." And the idea was born.
I have a bit of a vision for having a logo that's flexible colour wise - i.e., it could be red and white, or blue and white, or red and blue for example (allowing it to be against a variety of fabric colours) - and the image attached is a VERY rough (and poorly designed by yours truly) idea of what I envisioned. Just had to mock up what was in my head. By no means, feel like you have to stick to it, even colour wise.
In fact, even this weekend, one of my friends suggested the logo be an illustration/cartoon of people having a picnic being caught by the police with the name somewhere in there...I realise that might be more work but I thought that was a cool idea too, so I'm super open to your creativity/fresh angles/ideas.
The vibe is classic retro with an edge. It's meant to be a bit of a nod to how wild and sometimes ludicrous the world has been the last couple years as we've all been navigating something so unprecedented.

title: Tradition meets Tech: design a logo for our Machine Learning assisted Golf app
description:
We’re building “Unbogify” – an app for golfers to record their golf swing, analyze it and get help from a professional coach.
Our app allows golfers to record videos of their swings during a practice session and have them automatically cut into small 3 second clips to reduce file size compared to regularly recorded videos by a factor of 10.
Recorded clips can be annotated with a rating how good the shot was, what type of shot it was (was it a straight shot or curved? if curved, what kind of curve?), which club has been used and more. All this information will be helpful for a coach during analysis.
We’re also providing tools to analyze the video afterwards. A player (or coach) can draw lines, rectangles and circles to mark certain points during the shot, and play the video forwards and backwards in slow motion. It’s also possible to compare two swings in a side-by-side view.
Currently these two feature are the core features of our app:
- Record videos and have them automatically cut into tiny clips
- Analyze and compare the recorded videos
In later versions we plan to connect players with golf coaches all around the world with our “Coach Connect” feature. Golfers can record their shots and share them with coaches. Coaches can then look at these shots and comment and mark certain things using the drawing tools. This will be our third core feature.
So the core functionality of our app can probably best summarized as “record, analyze, and learn” but depending on our user’s demand we might add or change functionality in later versions.
**Now we need a logo!**
Since we’re primarily building an app for smartphones the logo should work especially great on small sizes or when used as app icon. Golf itself is a very traditional sport that usually goes along with vintage style and traditional imaging that often looks retro and dusty. We are not only a golf startup but also a technology company which is usually quite the opposite of traditional golf.
That means we’re looking for a logo that is appealing to golf players who are used to traditional / retro / vintage style but still has a “tech flavor”, that combines the design of traditional golf and modern technology. We prefer "modern" over "traditional" but if you have an idea how to combine both, maybe even in a playful way: we're very open to your creative ideas! However, this is not a must.
Also: a mascot would be super nice. Something like a small bird (because a so called “birdie” is something good in Golf) or maybe a cartoonized eagle (because if you play an “eagle” that’s even better than a “birdie”) or an albatros (which is even better than an eagle and even most professional golfers never reach in their entire career). This might also be nice to have but is not required!
Maybe something that I would describe as “playful but still serious” would be nice. Something that in the same way attracts both a 55 years old manager who is an avid golfer as well as a 18 years old student who aims to become a professional golfer.
other_notes:
We're open to your ideas. While we can imagine to have a mascot to stand out it is not a must. A thoroughly designed logo is more important than having a mascot at all cost. If you're a good illustrator we'd love to have a mascot in our logo and potentially use it in different variations in our app, but as mentioned, it's nothing we require and if the logo looks great without a mascot, we're happy with that too.
Colorwise: it should be something that is green or works well with green because golf is all around "green".
